    descriptionEn: 'From 431 to 404 BCE, the Athenian Empire and the Spartan alliance fought for hegemony over the Greek world. The war had three phases: the Archidamian War (431-421), the disastrous Sicilian Expedition (415-413), and the Decelean War (413-404). Athens dominated at sea, Sparta on land. In 404 BCE Athens surrendered, tore down its Long Walls, and dissolved the Delian League. The war transformed the Greek world; Thucydides\' "History of the Peloponnesian War" became a classic of Western historiography. Socrates served as a hoplite in the conflict.',
