    descriptionEn: 'In 184 CE, Zhang Jiao of Julu, using the Taoist Way of Peace as his organization, launched a massive peasant rebellion with the slogan "The Azure Heaven is dead; the Yellow Heaven shall arise." Rebels wore yellow scarves, giving them the name "Yellow Turbans." The uprising quickly spread across eight provinces with hundreds of thousands of followers. The Han court lifted the ban on political factions and authorized provincial recruitment to suppress the rebellion, with generals like Huangfu Song, Zhu Jun, and Cao Cao leading the campaign. Zhang Jiao died of illness that year and the main force was crushed by year\'s end, but remnants continued fighting for years. Critically, the court granted provincial governors extensive military and civil powers to deal with the crisis—directly leading to the fragmentation of the empire into warlord domains and setting the stage for the Three Kingdoms.',
