    summaryEn: 'A diplomatic congress that redrew Europe\'s map after the Napoleonic Wars, establishing the Concert of Europe that maintained relative peace for nearly a century.',
    description: '1814年9月至1815年6月，在奥地利外交大臣梅特涅的主持下，欧洲各国君主和外交官齐聚维也纳，召开了世界近代史上最大规模的外交会议。会议的核心原则是"正统主义"（恢复法国大革命前的合法王朝）和"势力均衡"（防止任何一国独霸欧洲）。主要决定包括：恢复波旁王朝在法国的统治，建立德意志邦联以替代神圣罗马帝国，荷兰与比利时合并为尼德兰联合王国，普鲁士和奥地利获得补偿性领土扩张。拿破仑"百日王朝"期间会议并未中断。维也纳体系（又称"欧洲协调"）在此后近一个世纪中基本维持了欧洲的大国和平，直到第一次世界大战的爆发。',
    descriptionEn: 'From September 1814 to June 1815, under the presidency of Austrian Foreign Minister Metternich, European monarchs and diplomats gathered in Vienna for the largest diplomatic congress in modern history. The core principles were "legitimacy" (restoring pre-revolutionary dynasties) and "balance of power" (preventing any single state from dominating Europe). Key decisions included: restoring the Bourbon monarchy in France, creating the German Confederation in place of the Holy Roman Empire, uniting Holland and Belgium into the United Kingdom of the Netherlands, and awarding compensatory territorial gains to Prussia and Austria. The Congress continued through Napoleon\'s "Hundred Days." The Vienna System (Concert of Europe) largely preserved great-power peace in Europe for nearly a century, until the outbreak of World War I.',
